text.section:
The duties and functions of the commission shall be to:
Advise the secretary of the Tourism, Arts and Heritage Cabinet and agencies within the cabinet on matters relating to African-American heritage;
Encourage other public and private agencies within the areas of the arts, the humanities, and the sciences to incorporate the African-American influence when developing programs on the history and heritage of Kentucky;
Represent a network of groups and individuals interested or involved in promoting awareness of African-American heritage in Kentucky;
Advocate the preservation, conservation, and interpretation of significant buildings, sites, neighborhoods, documents, artifacts, and lifeways that represent and embody African-American heritage;
Recognize and sanction projects which advance wider knowledge of African-Americans' impact on life in Kentucky; and
Coordinate an initiative to protect, preserve, and promote the history of the Underground Railroad in Kentucky, in accordance with KRS 171.812.
